Fifteen House Democrats have called to replenish the small business relief fund despite House Speaker Nancy Pelosi’s (D-CA) objections.
On Thursday morning, the Small Business Administration’s (SBA) small business relief fund, otherwise known as the Paycheck Protection Program (PPP), officially ran out of money.
Rep. Jason Crow (D-CO) said, “The @SBAgov ’s Paycheck Protection Program has just run out of money, leaving business owners who are trying to pay their employees stranded.
— Rep. Jason Crow (@RepJasonCrow) April 16, 2020Rep. Diana DeGette (D-CO) said, “Congress must immediately replenish funds for the Paycheck Protection Program.
We have to get this right.”Congress must immediately replenish funds for the Paycheck Protection Program.